[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 7/100 done id=gsm8k_test_93 prediction='36' gold='36' correct=True vote_counts={'44': 1, '36.3': 1, "Let \\( G \\) represent Gerald's original running time for the 400-meter hurdles in seconds.\n\nAccording to the problem:\n- Lee was originally capable of running the 400-meter hurdles 2 seconds faster than Gerald.\n- Therefore, Lee’s original time was \\( G - 2 \\) seconds.\n\nGiven:\n- Lee now takes 38 seconds to complete the race.\n\nWe set up the equation:\n\\[\nG - 2 = 38\n\\]\n\nSolving for \\( G \\):\n\\[\nG = 38 + 2\n\\]\n\\[\nG = 40\n\\]\n\nThus, before the diet improvement, Gerald took 40 seconds.\n\nWith the improved diet, Gerald's speed increased by 10%. To find the new time it takes him to complete the race:\n\nFirst, calculate the percentage increase:\n\\[\n10\\% = \\frac{1}{10}\n\\]\n\nThen multiply his original time (40 seconds) by this factor:\n\\[\n40 \\times \\frac{1}{10} = 4 \\text{ seconds}\n\\]\n\nFinally, subtract this increase from his original time:\n\\[\n40 - 4 = 36 \\text{ seconds}\n\\]\n\nTherefore, with his improved diet, Gerald can now complete the 400-meter hurdles in **36 seconds**.": 1, '36.36': 1, '36': 3, '39.6': 1}
