[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 14/100 path 5/8 answer="First, let's find out how many crabs Bo has:\nBo has 40 crabs\n\nNext, we know Monic has 4 fewer crabs than Bo:\nMonic has 40 - 4 = 36 crabs\n\nThen, we can determine how many crabs Rani has since she has ten more than Monic:\nRani has 36 + 10 = 46 crabs\n\nNow, to find the total number of crabs the three have together, we add their amounts:\nTotal crabs = Rani's crabs + Monic's crabs + Bo's crabs\nTotal crabs = 46 + 36 + 40\nTotal crabs = 122\n\nTherefore, the total number of crabs they have together is 122."
