[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 24/100 path 5/8 answer="Let B represent the number of boys.\nSince there are 3 times as many girls as boys, G = 3B.\nGiven B = 30, we can substitute to find the number of girls:\nG = 3 * 30 = 90.\nNow, let N represent the number of non-gendered children.\nWe're told that N = 1/10 * B.\nSubstituting the given value of B (30) gives us:\nN = 1/10 * 30 = 3.\nTo find the total number of children in the class, we sum up the numbers of boys, girls, and non-gendered children:\n\nTotal Children = Boys + Girls + Non-Gendered Children\n                = 30 + 90 + 3\n                = 123\n\nTherefore, the classroom has 123 total children."
