fter completing the 6500 steps, he still had 10000 - 6500 = 3500 steps remaining to reach his goal. However, there seems to be a mistake here because if he had already completed all required steps without needing further jogging, it would mean no more jogging was necessary.\n\nTo correct the calculation, assume he initially had 10000 steps minus the": 1}
