[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 45/100 path 7/8 answer='Let \\( x \\) be the amount Elvis saves each day in the first half of April. Thus, he saves \\( 2x \\) each day in the second half of April.\n\nThe total savings can be expressed as:\n\\[ (x + 2x)(\\frac{30}{30}) = 1125 \\]\n\\[ 3x \\cdot 1 = 1125 \\]\n\\[ 3x = 1125 \\]\n\nSolving for \\( x \\):\n\\[ x = \\frac{1125}{3} \\]\n\\[ x = 375 \\]\n\nSo, Elvis needs to save $375 each day in the first half of April.\n\nFor the second half of April:\n\\[ 2x = 2 \\times 375 = \\$\\boxed{750} \\]'
