[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 47/100 path 1/8 answer='Elise wrote the whole alphabet twice, so that’s 2 * 26 = 52 letters.\nThen she wrote half of the alphabet once, which is 26 / 2 = 13 letters.\nSo far, she has written 52 + 13 = 65 letters.\nNext, she re-writes all these 65 letters, adding them back onto what she previously wrote. This gives us a total of 65 + 65 = <<65+65=130>>130 letters.\nTherefore, Elise has written a total of 130 letters.'
