[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 4/8 answer="First, let us calculate how many points each student has:\n\n- Adam has 50 points.\n  \n- Betty collected 30% more than Adam, so:\n  Betty’s points = 50 + (50 * 0.3) = 50 + 15 = 65 points.\n\n- Marta collected 3 times as many points as Tom, and Tom has 30 points less than Betty:\n  Let Tom's points = T.\n  Marta's points = 3T.\n  Since Tom has 30 points less than Betty, we have:\n  T = Betty's points - 30 = 65 - 30 = 35 points.\n  Therefore, Marta’s points = 3 * 35 = 105 points.\n\nNow, we sum up all their points to find out the total number of points collected by the class:\nTotal points = Adam's points + Betty's points + Marta's points + Tom's points\n             = 50 + 65 + 105 + 35\n\nLet's calculate the total:\nTotal points = 50 + 65 + 105 + 35 = 255 points.\n\nTo determine how many points the class is missing to reach the trip requirement of 400 points:\nPoints needed = 400 - Total points\n              = 400 - 255\n              = 145 points.\n\nTherefore, the class is missing 145 points to go on the trip."
