[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 7/8 answer="First, we calculate how many points Betty got. Since Betty collected 30% more than Adam:\nBetty's points = Adam's points + (Adam's points * 30/100) \n                = 50 + (50 * 30/100)\n                = 50 + 15\n                = 65\n\nNext, we find out how many points Marta has. Marta collected 3 times more points than Tom:\nMarta's points = 3 * Tom's points\n               = 3 * (30)\n\nNow, let's calculate the points each person has so far:\nAdam: 50 points\nMartha: 3 * (30) = 90 points\nTom: 30 points\nBetty: 65 points\n\nAdding these together gives us the total points before adding anything from Marta and Tom's contributions:\nTotal points = Adam's points + Martha's points + Tom's points + Betty's points\n            = 50 + 90 + 30 + 65\n            = 235\n\nSince the problem doesn't specify what amount Marta and Tom have added, I'll assume they contributed their full amounts without further information:\nMarta's points (as calculated): 90 points\nTom's points: 30 points\n\nNow let's add up their contributions:\nMarta's additional points: 90\nTom's additional points: 30\n\nCombined contributions: 90 + 30 = 120\n\nFinally, we subtract the total points accumulated so far from the required 400 points to find out how many more points the class still needs:\n\nRequired points: 400\nAccumulated points: 235 + 120 = 35"
