[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 3/8 answer='To find the total area to be painted, we first calculate the area of each pair of opposite walls:\n\n- North wall: \\( 10 \\times 8 = 80 \\) sq ft\n- South wall: \\( 10 \\times 8 = 80 \\) sq ft\n\nFor the East and West walls:\n- East wall: \\( 5 \\times 8 = 40 \\) sq ft\n- West wall: \\( 5 \\times 8 = 40 \\) sq ft\n\nNow, we sum up all these areas:\n\\[ 80 + 80 + 40 + 40 = 240 \\text{ sq ft} \\]\n\nNext, since one gallon covers 20 square feet:\n\\[ \\frac{240}{20} = 12 \\text{ gallons needed} \\]\n\nAt $12 per gallon, the total cost will be:\n\\[ 12 \\text{ gallons} \\times \\$12/\\text{gallon} = \\$\\boxed{144}\\]'
