[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 85/100 path 4/8 answer='First, calculate the total number of scoops of mashed potatoes Gomer ate:\nHe ate 5 less than 23 scoops, so he ate 23 - 5 = 18 scoops.\n\nNext, find out how many scoops one scoop represents:\nIt takes 3 less than 6 scoops of mashed potatoes to make 1 scoop, which equals 6 - 3 = 3 scoops per potato.\n\nFinally, determine how many potatoes Gomer used:\nSince each scoop represents 3 potatoes, 18 scoops would mean 18 / 3 = 6 potatoes.\n\nTherefore, Gomer ate 6 potatoes.'
