[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 10/100 path 1/3 answer="Jordan spends 2 * 7 = 14 hours on his job each week.\nHe would make 14 * 10 = $<14*10=140>140 from his job.\n\nJordan would spend 14 * 2 = 28 hours playing video games.\nSince he can't play two games at once while working, he'd have enough time for only 28 / 2 = 14 hours of gaming during work days.\nFor those 14 hours, Jordan would earn 14 * 2 = $<14*2=28>28 from video games.\n\nTotal he would make working instead of playing video games is 140 + 28 = $<140+28=168>168.\nThat's how I arrived at the answer of $168."
