[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 37/100 path 1/3 answer="Let C be the original cost per helium balloon and B be the number of balloons filled on the first day.\n\nC + B = 900\nTwo days later, the original cost becomes C + 20 dollars for each balloon, making it (B + 20) times more expensive.\n\nAfter the increase, 170 balloons are filled at this increased rate:\n\n(C + 20)(B + 20) = $170\n\nSubstituting B = 900 - C into the second equation yields:\n((900 - C) + 20)((900 - C) + 20) = $170\n(920 - C)^2 = $170\nsqrt(920 - C) = √$170\n\nHowever, since we don't have enough information with the provided data to solve this problem accurately due to insufficient values or variables related to individual pricing and volume needed."
